Gombe state Governor, Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya has commended the National Judiciary for sitting a division of Court of Appeal in Gombe opining that it will bring justice closer to the people The Governor who inspected the level of progress of work on the complex preparatory to the take-off of the Gombe division of Court of Appeal, expressed satisfaction with the progress so far made describing it as very encouraging. Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya on Thursday inspected facilities at the temporary complex in company of his Deputy, Dr. Manassah Daniel Jatau, members of the State Executive Council and top judicial officials led by the State Acting Chief Judge, Justice Mu’azu Pindiga went round the appellate court’s complex to assess the quality of work and readiness of the facility for commencement of judicial activities. While Speaking to Journalists after the inspection tour, the Governor expressed satisfaction with the quality and standard of the renovation, noting that the work has met the required specifications. He noted that, with a division of the court of appeal now in place, clients within Gombe and the neighbouring states will have easy access to justice whenever the need arises. He described access to justice as one of the cardinal principles of democracy and human rights, lauding the President of the Court of Appeal, Justice Zainab Bulkachuwa for bringing a division of the appellate court to Gombe. He said that “Yola in Adamawa and Jos in Plateau states used to be the only nearest Courts of Appeal from Gombe but with the Gombe division of the appellate court that is about to take off, clients in Gombe and other neighboring states within the region can access justice at their doorsteps”. Trump says US forces killed al-Qaida leader Qassim al-Rimi… CBN injects $218.41m, CNY 18m into retail SMIS Buhari making false claims on security ― PDP PDP chieftain empowers Bauchi youths ALSO READ: CBN injects $218.41m, CNY 18m into retail SMIS The Governor said the temporary complex is provided by the state government and renovated to fast track the take-off of the court in Gombe and provide the desired comfort to dispense Justice with equity and fairness pending the completion of the permanent site. The governor later inspected the residential accommodation provided for the court of appeal staff at the Shehu Abubakar government lodge. Earlier in his remarks, the state Acting Chief Judge, Justice Mu’azu Pindiga thanked Governor Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya for the prompt release of the funds used in renovating the court facility. He said the State High and the Appellate Courts will continue to work in synergy to ensure the quick dispensation of justice to all. It will be recalled that Governor Inuwa Yahaya had recently approved both permanent and temporary sites for the take-off of a division of a Court of Appeal in Gombe state. A 7- man team, led by the presiding judge of Jos division of the Court of Appeal, Justice Adzira Gana Mshelia, had earlier visited the state on a facility tour of both the permanent and temporary sites as contained in a statement by Ismaila Uba Misilli, Senior Special Assistant, Media, and Publicity to the Governor. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE. PREMATURE EJACULATION, SMALL SIZE FINALLY CURED NATURALLY IN 2 WEEKS FOR BIGGER, LONGER, HARDER SEXIER SEX WITH NEW MAN MACHINE